One other note about who is hurting <TIMEX2 val="PRESENT_REF" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="1998-10-13T18:40:16.68" anchor_dir="AS_OF" comment="">these days</TIMEX2>.
We learned Harvard University's giant endowment lost $1.3 billion.
The Wall Street Journal reports <TIMEX2 val="1998-10-13" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">today</TIMEX2> a number of top colleges and
universities have been hurt by the market decline around the world.
They are vulnerable because they have been using aggressive investment
strategies to try building their endowments.
